724 // Replace G with a simple tail call to bitcast(F). Also (unless
725 // MergeFunctionsPDI holds) replace direct uses of G with bitcast(F),
726 // delete G. Under MergeFunctionsPDI, we use G itself for creating
727 // the thunk as we preserve the debug info (and associated instructions)
728 // from G's entry block pertaining to G's incoming arguments which are
729 // passed on as corresponding arguments in the call that G makes to F.
730 // For better debugability, under MergeFunctionsPDI, we do not modify G's
731 // call sites to point to F even when within the same translation unit.
